text: Hancock County is a county found in the U.S. state of Mississippi. As of the 2020 census, 46,053 people lived there. Its county seat is Bay St. Louis. The county was created in 1812. It is named for Founding Father John Hancock. The county is along the Gulf of Mexico and the state line with Louisiana. == References == Category:1810s establishments in Mississippi Territory Category:1812 establishments in the United States Category:Mississippi counties
